{{Top|leg|title=''Imperial''-class repulsortank}}
The '''''Imperial''-class''', or '''''Imperial''-series repulsortank''', was a line of military vehicles made by [[Ubrikkian Industries/Legends|Ubrikkian Industries]]. Three versions of the tank were created; [[Imperial Repulsortank 1-L|light]], [[Imperial Repulsortank 1-M|medium]], and [[Imperial-class 1-H repulsortank/Legends|heavy]] variants. The designation applied to the amount of armament carried by each variant tank as all three tanks of the ''Imperial''-class shared the same chassis design. The heavy variant of the Imperial repulsortank was the standard production model.

==''Imperial''-class repulsortank variants==
[[File:1-L.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Imperial Repulsortank 1-L]]

===Light Imperial Repulsortank===
{{Main|Imperial Repulsortank 1-L}}
The cheapest version of the ''Imperial''-class repulsortank, the 1-L lacked the main gun found on the heavier variants. It required a crew of only two to operate&mdash;driver and [[Gunner/Legends|gunner]]&mdash;and had space for either the [[Sergeant/Legends|sergeant]] or [[Platoon/Legends|platoon]] [[Sergeant major/Legends|sergeant major]]. It mounted a single [[Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc./Legends|Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc.]] [[Mark 3/S Medium Blaster Cannon]].

[[File:1-M.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Imperial Repulsortank 1-M]]

===Medium Imperial Repulsortank===
{{Main|Imperial Repulsortank 1-M}}
The medium Imperial repulsortank was produced in limited numbers and intended for use by [[Platoon/Legends|platoon]] officers to command their units in the field. It required a crew of three to operate&mdash;driver, gunner, and commanding [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]]&mdash;with enough space for the sergeant major and communications equipment as well. The 1-M mounted a Merr-Sonn Mark 3/S Medium Blaster Cannon and a [[Heavy repeating blaster/Legends|heavy repeating blaster]].

[[File:1-H.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Imperial Repulsortank 1-H]]

===Heavy Imperial Repulsortank===
{{Main|Imperial-class 1-H repulsortank/Legends}}
The heavy Imperial repulsortank was the most widely produced of the ''Imperial''-class and required a crew of four to operate&mdash;driver, two gunners, and the commanding sergeant. Considered to be a [[Squad/Legends|squad]] level unit in itself for the purposes of the Order of Battle, the 1-H mounted a Merr-Sonn [[Mark 4e/S heavy laser cannon|Mark 4e/S Heavy Laser Cannon]] and a Mark 3/S Medium Blaster Cannon. Of the first 1,500 tanks produced, 1,420 were assigned to the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first]] [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], and eighty to the [[Imperial Hammers Elite Armor Unit/Legends|Imperial Hammers Elite Armor Unit]].

